WEBVTT

NOTE This is a caption file for CSS Grid Layout Tutorial

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Hello everyone! Welcome to this CSS Grid tutorial.

00:00:03.500 --> 00:00:07.000
Today we'll learn how to create responsive layouts
using CSS Grid.

00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:11.000
Let's start by defining a grid container.
[keyboard typing]

00:00:11.500 --> 00:00:15.000
We use "display: grid" to create a grid container.

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:19.000
Then we define columns with "grid-template-columns".

00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:23.000
For example: grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:27.000
This creates three equal columns.
[mouse clicking]

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:31.000
Now let's add some gap between grid items.

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:35.000
We use the "gap" property for this.

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:39.000
gap: 20px; will add 20 pixels of space
between all grid items.

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:43.000
Let's see how this looks in the browser.
[browser refreshing]

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:47.000
Perfect! Now we have a responsive grid layout.

00:00:47.500 --> 00:00:51.000
You can also use grid-template-areas
for more complex layouts.

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:55.000
This allows you to name different sections
of your grid.

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:59.000
For example, you can define header, sidebar,
main content, and footer areas.

00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:03.000
[keyboard typing]
Let me show you an example.

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:07.000
We define the template areas like this:
grid-template-areas...

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:11.000
Then we assign each grid item to an area
using grid-area property.

00:01:11.500 --> 00:01:15.000
This makes your CSS much more readable
and maintainable.

00:01:15.500 --> 00:01:19.000
CSS Grid is incredibly powerful for creating
modern web layouts.

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:23.000
Practice these concepts, and you'll be creating
amazing layouts in no time!

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:26.000
Thanks for watching! See you in the next tutorial.
[upbeat music]
